snippet.title: The mind of a Genius: Kamal Haasan on Art, life and passion | Gobinath
snippet.description:
Enquiries:
talk2gobinath@gmail.com

#Gobinath #kamalhaasan #ulaganayagan #art #life #passion #legacy #podcast #cinema #tamilcinema #legacyofexcellence 

Stay ahead with direct updates from Gobinath ‚Äî interviews, insights, and powerful voices.
Join the official WhatsApp Channel today:
https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Vb5gNn82Jl8DSfwhUM3G

In this powerful episode, Gobinath sits down with the legendary Ulaganayagan Kamal Haasan‚Äîa visionary who has not just acted in cinema but revolutionized it. 

With fearless creativity, deep philosophy, and decades of reinvention, Kamal reflects on a life lived in service of art. From listening to the heart over algorithms to exploring aging, AI, acting, and mortality, this conversation dives into the mind of a master.

From listening to the heart over algorithms to exploring aging, AI, and the ethics of cinema, Kamal opens up about:

 ‚Ä¢ His constant reinvention and evolution as an artist
 ‚Ä¢ The humbling moments that shaped his self-awareness
 ‚Ä¢ Learning from the ancients, yet daring to innovate
 ‚Ä¢ Acting not as imitation but as raw, requested ‚Äúmisbehavior‚Äù
 ‚Ä¢ Balancing perfection with beautiful imperfection
 ‚Ä¢ Time, discipline, mortality‚Äîand the pursuit of artistic immortality
 ‚Ä¢ The philosophies behind his cinema: for whom, and why
 ‚Ä¢ The tension between market demands and meaningful messaging
 ‚Ä¢ Minimalism, nostalgia, and the emotional universality of war and motherhood
 ‚Ä¢ His Gandhian turn and his deeply underrated contributions as a lyricist
 ‚Ä¢ Tamil‚Äôs rhythmic beauty and its global poetic power
 ‚Ä¢ The role of cinema in shaping society and the next generation
 ‚Ä¢ Corporate capitalism, global politics, and center-aligned balance
 ‚Ä¢ Parenting, emotional intelligence, and legacy beyond screens
 ‚Ä¢ His take on AI, knowledge, and the evolving boundaries of intelligence
 ‚Ä¢ The behind-the-scenes genius of the technicians behind Thug Life
 ‚Ä¢ And his reflections on the title Thug Life and its connection to Nayakan

Kamal also shares heartfelt memories from his childhood, honors icons like Sivaji, Kannadasan, Periyar, and Kalaignar, and lays bare what continues to drive his tireless journey as a creator.

This episode is more than an interview‚Äîit‚Äôs a philosophical masterclass, a celebration of art, and a tribute to the spirit of relentless curiosity.

A must-watch for cinephiles, thinkers, artists, and dreamers who believe in the power of storytelling to change the world.

 ‚Ä¢ Balancing perfection with beautiful imperfection
 ‚Ä¢ Time, discipline, mortality‚Äîand the pursuit of artistic immortality
 ‚Ä¢ The philosophies behind his cinema: for whom, and why
 ‚Ä¢ The tension between market demands and meaningful messaging
 ‚Ä¢ Minimalism, nostalgia, and the emotional universality of war and motherhood
 ‚Ä¢ His Gandhian turn and his deeply underrated contributions as a lyricist
 ‚Ä¢ Tamil‚Äôs rhythmic beauty and its global poetic power
 ‚Ä¢ The role of cinema in shaping society and the next generation
 ‚Ä¢ Corporate capitalism, global politics, and center-aligned balance
 ‚Ä¢ Parenting, emotional intelligence, and legacy beyond screens
 ‚Ä¢ His take on AI, knowledge, and the evolving boundaries of intelligence
 ‚Ä¢ The behind-the-scenes genius of the technicians behind Thug Life
 ‚Ä¢ And his reflections on the title Thug Life and its connection to Nayakan

Kamal also shares heartfelt memories from his childhood, honors icons like Sivaji, Kannadasan, Periyar, and Kalaignar, and lays bare what continues to drive his tireless journey as a creator.

This episode is more than an interview‚Äîit‚Äôs a philosophical masterclass, a celebration of art, and a tribute to the spirit of relentless curiosity.

A must-watch for cinephiles, thinkers, artists, and dreamers who believe in the power of storytelling to change the world.

Everyone argues over the unaddressed tempo in the Gokuldham Society. Bapuji intervenes and asks them to come up with a solution rather than arguing with each other. Jethalal has a heartfelt conversation with his grandfather. Later, he revisits memories of the Republic Day celebration and decides to call Babitaji to appreciate Mahila Mandal's efforts for the preparations. Jethalal reads the letter to Babitaji that she found in Iyer's book. It was a love letter that he translates completely for Babitaji. Later, Jethalal's fear comes true, when Sundar arrives at his home and starts dancing.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in 'Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The residents of the housing society, help each other find solutions when they face common, real-life challenges and get involved in sticky situations.

About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji.

snippet.title: FilterCopy | If Doctors Could Hear Your Thoughts | Ft. Eisha Chopra & Baishali Sinha
snippet.description:
What‚Äôs the one thought you never want your doctor to find out? 

Well, a doctor may not hear your thoughts but are you listening to your body? If you're feeling breathless, tight in the chest, or dealing with a constant cough, don‚Äôt brush it off. These could be signs of asthma. This Asthma Awareness Month, take charge of your lung health.

Visit www.breathefree.com or download the BreatheFree app: https://l.breathefree.in/DownloadTheApp

Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. snippet.title: FRUIT MIXER | Colorful Healthy Fruits Mixed Recipe | Summer Health Fruit Recipe Making in Village
snippet.description:
Today in our village, we made a colorful and healthy fruit mixer using fresh fruits. We included apples, oranges, watermelon, strawberries, kiwis, mangoes, papayas, jackfruit, and more, along with soaked almond gum, basil seeds, and pure honey for added taste and health benefits.

The video beautifully cuts and shows all the fruits, making it refreshing and satisfying to watch. This natural recipe is perfect for all seasons, especially summer, and is a great healthy fruit recipe for kids.

Enna venum unakku  
Kotti kotti kidakku  
Innum enna venum unakku  
Sorgam ingu irukku  

Kallam ulle nenju  
Kadhalendra nanju  
Kannai moodi kondu  
Ennai mattum konju  

Enna venum unakku  
Kotti kotti kidakku

Sugar baby en  
Sugar baby  
Sugar baby en  
Sugar baby (2)  

Anaikka vaa  
Anaikka vaa (2)

Kotti kotti kidakku  
Innum enna venum unakku  
Sorgam ingu irukku  

Kaliyugam idhu  
Kadal eriyudhu  
Pagai nerunguthu  
Padai konduva.. va  

Varuguthu Puli  
Vilaguthu Nadhi  
Adi Athiradi  
Edhirigal Bali  

Vaal. Neelam Vedham Odhudhu  
Veesum Kaathule Vesham Maaruthu  
Indha Pollatha Ooru VeNaamadi  
Ni Vanthaal Sari..  
En Ulage Neeyadi..

If love is a crime, my baby is criminal. 
criminal criminal criminal criminal. 
I pay the fine to the time, 
without mining him cynical. 
cynical cynical cynical. 
If being rich is a sin, 
I wanna be a sinner sinner sinner sinner. 
Now I am married to the game
 I am gonna be the winner winner winner winner.

snippet.description:

Get your very own space selfie for FREE at: http://spaceselfie.com

Big thanks to my friends at @T-Mobile for supporting this project in celebration of T-Satellite, the only satellite + mobile network with seamless connection.

And thanks to my friends at Google Pixel for being the best phone to display all the space selfies on  @madebygoogle   #googlepartner. 

https://www.instagram.com/teampixel/ 

Thanks to our Build team at Tyvak International for helping us bring SAT GUS to life! https://tyvak.eu/
And of course  @EverydayAstronaut 

With special thanks to the Explosives Research Lab at Colorado School of Mines https://erl.mines.edu/

For the first 2-3 months, winner may be notified via phone call instead of winning game piece. If a monthly prize is unclaimed/forfeited, it will be awarded via 2nd chance drawing. snippet.title: Bhide aur Jethalal ki Ladai! | FULL MOVIE | Part 1 | Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Watch the FULL MOVIE of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSk2_rPKNCDcjNAA8vaDN-E&si=rC5AotwLD2r3MHna

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.description:
Shiva Rajkumar Speech at Thuglife Audio Launch Event on Sreshth Movies.
